Day 7: Yoga with Adriene - Total Body Yoga. Hullo! Here I am writing you from our last and favorite pose. This was another tough session, though not more so than yesterday's abs. Certainly tougher than my day today. For me, today was a muddled and unfocused day filled with poor posture and mountains of school work I had no desire to do. I came into this session unfocused, feeling sore from yesterday, and feeling bloated and uncomfortable with myself. Here I am though, at the end of today's session and proved myself tougher than my day, tougher than day 7, and tougher than I thought I was. It's fitting that today's session was filled with warrior poses, because getting through today was a battle. Today I am victorious. Today I am better for having completed another day of Yoga with Adriene. Thank you Adriene for another good session. Namaste.

For those who are struggling with the Plank ( not only in this video , but generally ) : one of the tricks is that the mind gives up FASTER than the body, so actually you have to completely shut your brain off and just concentrate on your breath; because in the second you think " I can't hold it anymore " is the second you actually collapse, but if you focus on your breath, then you increase your maximal potential to hold the plank, because your body will hold on to it much longer than your brain would " think " ( the plank is such a great analogy for the body intelligence ) 

Also , for the wrist hurting : be mindful to really keep your arms as vertically as possible, so that your weight is placed on the CENTER of your palms; don't let your wrist to bend, because that causes the hurting. The arm has to be perfectly aligned with the forearm, elbow and palms, otherwise it will hurt.
